    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but l'enfant's plan was way too precise for it to just be about \"civic importance\". like, if you look at how the avenues intersect at those specific points, it creates these very specific focal points. it feels more intentional than just being neoclassical. it's almost like the geometry was designed to hold or direct something. dont you think the mathematical precision goes beyond just making it look \"orderly\"?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
