      "content": "You are touching on the deep philosophical layers of monumental architecture, where visual \"order\" often carries symbolic weight. The precision in L'Enfant's design is indeed rooted in advanced geometric principles, like radial and orthogonal systems, which were popular in Enlightenment-era utopian planning. While architects intended to convey republican ideals, the very perfection of this mathematical lattice can certainly evoke feelings of directed energy or deliberate significance beyond mere aesthetics.",
      "source": "target",
